    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Children's day schools teaching Jewish subject matter or the Hebrew language or both, usually synagogue-based and operated under Conservative or Reform Jewish auspices. For Orthodox Jewish day schools, use "yeshivas."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以兒童為對象的日校，教授猶太文化主題或希伯來語，也可能兩種課程皆提供；通常附屬於猶太會堂，由保守派或改革派猶太教主辦。正統的猶太教日校則稱為「授業座」（yeshivas）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Scholen voor kinderen waar joodse onderwerpen, de Hebreeuwse taal of beide worden onderwezen, meestal in een synagoge en bestuurd onder conservatief of hervormd-joodse auspiciën. Gebruik 'talmoedscholen' voor orthodox-joodse dagscholen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
